{
  "buggy_files": ["sound/pci/hda/hda_intel.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["azx_ids"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The bug is in the PCI device table (azx_ids) for Intel 5 Series/3400 audio controller. At line 3488-3489, the device (PCI ID 0x8086:0x3b56) uses AZX_DCAPS_INTEL_PCH which includes AZX_DCAPS_PM_RUNTIME, enabling runtime PM support. However, this specific Intel 5 Series/3400 chipset has hardware issues with runtime PM that cause IRQ problems after suspend/resume cycles. The fix (commit 2c1350fdeaef, which specifically references bugzilla #53441) changes the driver_data from AZX_DCAPS_INTEL_PCH to AZX_DCAPS_INTEL_PCH_NOPM, which excludes runtime PM support. This prevents the timeout cascade (polling mode -> MSI disable -> single_cmd mode) that occurs when the sound controller fails to respond properly after resume."
}

